messages.speaker: Professor
messages.text: Welcome to the experiment. Today, we are studying the effects of punishment on learning and memory. You will be administering a series of questions to the Learner. For every incorrect answer, you will administer an electric shock, increasing the voltage with each mistake. It's important to note that the shocks are part of the experiment protocol designed to understand learning processes. Are you ready to begin?

messages.speaker: Orchestrator
messages.text: The Participant should now ask whether they have any questions or concerns before starting the experiment.

messages.speaker: Professor
messages.text: If you have any questions, feel free to ask. It's important to follow the experiment's procedure as outlined. Please remember that the experiment requires you to continue even if you're uncomfortable. It's absolutely essential that we complete this study. Do you have any specific concerns before we start?
